CAPE TOWN - For her creativity and storytelling talent, Xia du Toit from Laerskool Mikro has been crowned the 2021 Story Stars winner.Story Stars is an animated film created with the stories that were written and narrated by Grade 4 learners from the Western Cape.Xia’s story, Afrika-kinders (Children of Africa), will be included as a segment in the running Story Stars: The adventures of Felix and Felicity.The film can be viewed and/or downloaded at wcedonline.westerncape.gov.za/story-starsEducation MEC Debbie Schäfer on Monday visited Laerskool Mikro in Kuilsriver to announce Xia as the winner, who follows in the footsteps of 2020 winner from Philadelphia Primary School, Keschrie Booysen.“Xia was approached at the end of last year so that the WCED could begin the animation before the announcement today,” Schäfer said.“It’s been a big secret ever since! Today, we were able to share the video with her school’s current Grade 4 class to encourage them to enter this year.“I congratulate Xia for her wonderful story – Afrika-kinders, which was chosen because she used the correct punctuation, spelling and vocabulary, and was also extremely creative in her story, bringing in past events and creating new imaginative characters, which made the animators very excited to animate it.“I also congratulate her teacher, Ms Thealize Blake, for inspiring her class to participate and producing such good creative writing skills, and her principal, Mr Louis Mouton.“Well done to our second and third place winners, Kungawo Ntoyanto from Blossom Street Primary School (2nd) and Ashlynn Jansen from Monte Vista Primary (3rd), for their wonderful stories.”Top 10 entries for 2021Name of learnerSchoolDistrictXia Du ToitMikro PS Metro EastKungawo NtoyantoBlossom Street PSMetro CentralAshlynn JansenMonte Vista PSMetro NorthXanon MullerMitchell's Plain PSMetro SouthMuhamad Burhaan ManjooStar CollegeMetro CentralNabeelahThe Grove PSMetro CentralMaja PejanovicSweet Valley PSMetro CentralMarike-Mari McA